Definition: the choicest or most essential or most vital part of some idea or experience
Example: the gist of the prosecutor's argument; the heart and soul of the Republican Party; the nub of the story
Synonyms: substance, core, center, adj, all, important, central, centre, noun, location, Canada, r, Britain, essence, essential, gist, heart, heart_and_soul, inwardness, marrow, meat, meaningful, meaty, nub, pith, concise, pithy, sum, verb, social, summate, nitty-gritty, content, the, choicest, or, most, vital, part, of, some, idea, experience, prosecutor, s, argument, and, soul, Republican, Party, story
Category: noun.cognition
